article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 61, San Francisco 40
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Trae Clark scored 14 points and Lorenzo Keeler had 13 as Cal Poly beat San Francisco 61-40 Wednesday night. The Mustangs led throughout, racing to a 15-6 lead that they never gave up. Cal Poly (2-4) shot just 33 percent from the field but held the Dons to 24 percent and forced 17 turnovers. Wes Dipprey led the Mustangs with 10 rebounds, and Shawn Lewis added 10 points. Dior Lowhorn had 21 points and nine rebounds to lead San Francisco (5-3). The Dons have dropped two straight after opening the season 5-1. They lost to USC on Monday night.
